## API layer (F4 pattern)

Use **Axios** via `apiAxios` (from `lib/api-helpers/axios-instance.ts`) in all client-side module services.  
Use the fetch-based `apiClient` (from `lib/api-helpers/client.ts`) **only** in Server Components or Server Actions.

| Tool | Location | Rule |
|------|----------|------|
| `apiAxios` | `modules/*/services/*.service.ts` | Client hooks (TanStack Query) |
| `apiClient` | `lib/actions/`, RSC services | Server-only; never in `"use client"` files |
| TanStack Query | `modules/*/services/*.service.ts` | `useQuery` / `useMutation` for all client data fetching |
| Zustand | `lib/store/*.store.ts` | UI state only вЂ” never server data; never `fetch` inside stores |
| Zod validators | `lib/validators/*.ts` | Shared between Server Actions and client-side form validation |

### Service file convention

```ts
// modules/public/projects/services/projects.service.ts
import { useQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { apiAxios } from "@/src/lib/api-helpers";
import { API } from "@/src/lib/url-helpers";

export const projectKeys = {
  all: ["projects"] as const,
  list: (params?) => [...projectKeys.all, "list", params] as const,
};

export function useProjects(params?) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: projectKeys.list(params),
    queryFn: () => apiAxios.get(API.PROJECTS.LIST, { params }).then(r => r.data),
  });
}
```

## Modals

| Audience | Location | Rule |
|----------|----------|------|
| Public / user site | `modules/public/modals/` | `"use client"` вЂ” forms, dialogs, interest capture |
| Admin CMS | `modules/admin/modals/` | `"use client"` вЂ” CRUD previews, detail panels, confirmations |
| Feature-specific | `modules/{public\|admin}/<feature>/modals/` | OK when modal is used by one feature only |

- Never place modal components in `src/app/` вЂ” routes stay thin.
- Public modals must not import from admin modules; admin modals must not import from public modules.
- Barrel-export via `modals/index.ts` per audience folder.

## App Router patterns (use these)

| Concern | Pattern |
|---------|---------|
| Public data | **Server Components** вЂ” async page, fetch in component or module `services/` |
| SEO | **`generateMetadata()`** per `page.tsx` вЂ” never client DOM meta hacks |
| Forms (public) | **Server Actions** in `lib/actions/public.ts` + Zod validation |
| Admin CRUD | **Server Actions** in `lib/actions/admin.ts` + `requireAdmin()` + `revalidatePath()` |
| Auth guard | **`middleware.ts`** + admin `layout.tsx` calls `requireAdmin()` |
| Client interactivity | `"use client"` islands вЂ” forms, modals, uploads, animations |
| Client data fetching | `useQuery` / `useMutation` via `apiAxios` in module `services/` |
| Client UI state | Zustand stores in `lib/store/` вЂ” filters, modal open/close |
| Loading / error | `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx` per route segment |
| BFF / presign | `app/api/**/route.ts` Route Handlers only when needed |
| Images | `next/image` вЂ” never raw `<img>` for static assets |
| Links | `next/link` вЂ” never `<a href>` for internal navigation |
| Toasts | `sonner` (`toast.success` / `toast.error`) вЂ” never legacy Toaster DOM |

## Separation rules

| Layer | Location | Rule |
|-------|----------|------|
| Routes | `src/app/` | Thin вЂ” compose module components; no heavy logic inline |
| Public UI | `modules/public/` | Never import from `modules/admin/` |
| Admin UI | `modules/admin/` | Never import from `modules/public/` |
| Public modals | `modules/public/modals/` | User-facing dialogs only |
| Admin modals | `modules/admin/modals/` | CMS dialogs only вЂ” never in `app/` or inline in tables |
| Server Actions | `lib/actions/` | All mutations; validate with `lib/validators/` |
| API calls | `lib/api-helpers/` + module `services/` | Use `lib/url-helpers/api-endpoints.ts` |
| URLs | `lib/url-helpers/` | Never hardcode paths in components |
| shadcn | `components/ui/` | Presentational only |

## Forbidden вЂ” legacy & Replit (never add or copy)

**Old Next.js (Pages Router):**
- `pages/`, `_app.tsx`, `_document.tsx`
- `getServerSideProps`, `getStaticProps`, `getInitialProps`
- `next/head` for SEO
- `pages/api/*` (use `app/api/**/route.ts` instead)

**Old React / Replit SPA:**
- Code from `artifacts/zafora/` (Vite + react-router)
- `@replit/*` packages or Replit vite plugins
- `react-router-dom`, `BrowserRouter`, `<Routes>`
- Client-only SPA data loading for public pages when RSC fits
- `useSeoMeta` / `document.title` / manual `<meta>` injection in `useEffect`
- Orval/OpenAPI codegen: `api-spec`, `api-client-react`, `api-zod`, `useList*`, `useCreate*` hooks вЂ” **do not import in new code**
- Replit object storage / GCS sidecar paths (`127.0.0.1:1106`, `object-storage-web`)
- Duplicate `workplace/` or `lib/db` packages inside frontend
- `@tanstack/react-query` on **new** public pages (use RSC + Server Actions instead)
- Class components, `defaultProps`, legacy lifecycle methods
- `apiClient` (fetch-based) inside `"use client"` files вЂ” use `apiAxios` instead
- Raw `fetch()` calls inside client components вЂ” always go through `apiAxios`
- Zustand stores that call `fetch`/`axios` directly вЂ” put fetching in TanStack Query, Zustand = UI state only

**When touching legacy files:** refactor toward App Router + module structure; do not extend old patterns.

## Naming & imports

- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Server Actions file: `lib/actions/*.ts` with `"use server"` at top
- Services: `*.service.ts` or `list-leads.ts`
- Use `@/src/...` path alias
- Barrel exports via module `index.ts`

## Do not

- Create `pages/` directory
- Put business logic in `app/**/page.tsx` вЂ” delegate to modules
- Put modal components in `app/` вЂ” use `modules/public/modals/` or `modules/admin/modals/`
- Mix admin and public code in one component
- Hardcode API or route paths
- Import from `@/src/lib/api-client-react` in new code
- Use `apiClient` (fetch) inside `"use client"` files вЂ” use `apiAxios` instead
- Put server data (API responses) in Zustand вЂ” TanStack Query owns all server state
- Copy-paste from Replit artifacts without full App Router rewrite
- Remove existing libraries (framer-motion, sonner, etc.) вЂ” add only, never remove without confirming
